This paper focuses on the optimization of task offloading in vehicular networks, which is a subfield of computer networks. Therefore, cs.NI (Networks and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a learning-based algorithm to improve the quality of service, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. The paper also deals with the dynamics of the network, which can be modeled as a control problem, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible category. The paper also involves the design of a utility function, which is a common topic in information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with the allocation of computing resources, which is a topic in distributed computing, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a possible category as well.
